+-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Configuring google_compute_engine scripts to run at boot
========================================================

The rc scripts are not enabled by default, you can enable them using the
following commands:

	rcctl enable google_accounts_daemon
	rcctl enable google_clock_skew_daemon
	rcctl enable google_ip_forwarding_daemon

Add the following commands at /etc/rc.local in the following order:

	google_instance_setup
	google_network_setup
	google_metadata_script_runner --script-type=startup

Add the following commands at /etc/rc.shutdown:

	google_metadata_script_runner --script-type=shutdown

Then reboot your system
